 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Don&#8217;t get m=
e wrong. I think it&#8217;s great that Twitter is sharing revenue with the =
creators who drive it, and I&#8217;ll happily take the money. I got donuts =
to buy. And I love that some people are making more money from tweeting tha=
n they do in their day job; what a world!&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#82=
17;s just that Twitter is an easy toy example to make a bigger point:&#160;=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>It's useful to be aware of the trade-offs and=
 incentives pulling at you as (almost) everything turns into a liquid and l=
egible market.</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Liquid and legible markets are=
, on balance, a great thing. They&#8217;re a sign of progress&#8217; march.=
&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The market for </span><a href=3D"https://=
link.sbstck.com/redirect/541aa38a-861c-4895-9ca7-5e33aa8b9326?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: =
